Ben Zion Aryeh Leibish Halberstam (    ) known as "R' Ben Tzin", is the disputed Grand Rabbi of the Bobov Hasidic movement. Born in 1955 to Grand Rabbi Shlomo Halberstam of Bobov, the third Bobover Rebbe, Rabbi Ben Zion Aryeh Leibish Halberstam is regarded by many as the Bobover Rebbe ( " " , " ). Rabbi Ben Zion Halberstam is presently Rabbi in the Bobover synagogue in Brooklyn. Following the death of Grand Rabbi Naftali Zvi Halberstam in 2005, a dispute arose as to who should succeed him as Bobover Rebbe. Many claim the title for his younger brother Rabbi Ben Zion Halberstam, while many others claim the title for his son-in-law, Rabbi Mordechai Dovid Unger. A Beth Din is currently deciding this issue among other issues of the Bobover dispute. Disputed: Halberstam family tree
